    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted despite Test conditions factor falling below required Gradation 3. The shortfall is offset by the strength of evidence across all other 12 factors, the direct regulatory relevance of the ASTM F1717 test configuration, and the satisfactory quantitative validation metrics (all E/uval < 1.96, all QoI differences < 10%). Uncertainty quantification across material and geometric inputs has been performed and documented. The assessment team concurs that the FEA modeling framework is credible for the stated COU and supports regulatory submission.",
